IL6{serum}.name: Interleukin-6 in serum
IL6{serum}.description: Inflammatory cytokine circulating in blood serum; elevated in Crohn's disease patients

sgp130{serum}.name: Soluble gp130 in serum
sgp130{serum}.description: Natural inhibitor of IL-6 trans-signaling that sequesters the IL-6/sIL-6Rα complex in circulation

sR_IL6_sgp130{serum}.name: IL-6/sIL-6Rα/sgp130 complex in serum

CRP{serum}.name: C-reactive protein in serum
CRP{serum}.description: Acute-phase protein in circulation; used as a biomarker for inflammation in Crohn's disease

sR{serum}.name: Soluble IL-6 receptor in serum
sR{serum}.description: Soluble form of IL-6 receptor alpha (sIL-6Rα) in circulation; mediates trans-signaling

sR_IL6{serum}.name: IL-6/sIL-6Rα complex in serum
sR_IL6{serum}.description: Complex of IL-6 bound to soluble IL-6 receptor in circulation; key mediator of trans-signaling

Ab{serum}.name: Therapeutic antibody in serum
Ab{serum}.description: Anti-IL-6 or anti-IL-6Rα antibody in circulation

Ab_sR{serum}.name: Antibody-sIL-6Rα complex in serum
Ab_sR{serum}.description: Complex formed when therapeutic antibody binds to soluble IL-6 receptor in circulation

Ab_sR_IL6{serum}.name: Antibody-IL-6/sIL-6Rα complex in serum
Ab_sR_IL6{serum}.description: Complex formed when therapeutic antibody binds to IL-6/sIL-6Rα complex in circulation

CRP Suppression (%).name: CRP suppression percentage
CRP Suppression (%).description: Output metric measuring percent reduction in CRP levels due to therapeutic intervention

CRP (% of baseline).name: CRP percentage of baseline
